'''Tsurumaki Kofun''' (つるまきこふん) is an ancient Kofun located in {{ill|Isesaki City|en|伊勢崎市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isesaki City|qq=}}, {{ill|Gunma Prefecture|en|群馬県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gunma Prefecture|qq=}}, Japan. It has been developed into the '''Tsurumaki Kofun Historical Park''', equipped with parking facilities.<ref name="Kofunmap">[https://kofun.info/kofun/1892 Kofun map]</ref>
== Overview == The site was Historic Site1 as a city historic site on February 21, 1969 (Shōwa 44).<ref name="IsesakiCity">[https://www.city.isesaki.lg.jp/soshiki/kyoikubu/hogo/bunkazaihogo/shitei/shiseki/2703.html Isesaki City Official Website]</ref>
== Structure == * '''Mound'''<ref name="IsesakiCity" /> **''' Diameter: 34 meters<ref name="IsesakiCity" /> *** '''East-West: 35.5 meters<ref name="Kofunmap" />''' *** '''North-South: 32.5 meters<ref name="Kofunmap" />'''
